net.truelicense.api

Interface VendorLicenseManager

  • All Superinterfaces:
    ContextProvider<LicenseManagementContext>, LicenseManagementParametersProvider, LicenseManagementSchema

    public interface VendorLicenseManager
extends LicenseManagementSchema
    Defines the life cycle management operations for license keys in vendor applications alias key generators.

    A (checked) vendor license manager generally throws a LicenseManagementException if an operation fails.

    Author:
    Christian Schlichtherle
    See Also:
    UncheckedVendorLicenseManager.checked()

    • Method Detail

      • generateKeyFrom

        LicenseKeyGenerator generateKeyFrom(License bean)
                             throws LicenseManagementException
        Returns a license key generator for the given license bean.

        Calling this operation performs an initial authorization check.

        Parameters:
        bean - the license bean to process. This bean is not modified by the returned license key generator.
        Returns:
        A license key generator for the given license bean.
        Throws:
        LicenseManagementException

      • unchecked

        default UncheckedVendorLicenseManager unchecked()
        Adapts this vendor license manager so that it generally throws an UncheckedLicenseManagementException instead of a (checked) LicenseManagementException if an operation fails.
        Returns:
        the adapted unchecked vendor license manager.
        Since:
        TrueLicense 3.1.0
